The objective of the Splunk App for Aternity and Riverbed is to provide analytics and visualizations of the ingested AppInternals and Aternity data:
1. Objects under monitoring and their topology – such as an instance running on (which servers), and server tags are used to groups the servers
2. Metrics and delays for objects under monitoring; for example counts and aggregations of normal, slow, very slow transactions
3. Alerts – generated by AppInternals and sent via SNMP
4. Metric and location data for Business Activities ingested from Aternity
5. Data normalization and enrichment for out of the box integration with Splunk ITSI Module for Application Performance Monitoring

For documentation, see: http://portal.it-squared.net/?p=569

For any technical difficulties contact integrations.support@it-squared.net


RELEASE HISTORY
